<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Q. Na, H. Zeng &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema baishanzuense" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="baishanzuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema baishanzuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered to be a distinct species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1951" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of its deeply infundibuliform pileus, decurrent lamellae, smooth and long ellipsoid basidiospores, sarcodimitic tramal tissues, cylindrical or clavate caulocystidia, and a lignicolous habitat (
<bibRefCitation author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B58" refString="Singer, R, 1986. The Agaricales in modern taxonomy, 4th edn. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" title="The Agaricales in modern taxonomy, 4 th edn." year="1986">Singer 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Redhead, SA" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B50" refString="Redhead, SA, 1986. Mycological observations: 17-20, nomenclatural notes on some omphaloid genera in Canada: Chrysomphalina, Rickenella, Gerronema, Omphalina. Acta Mycologica Sinica Suppl: 297-304." title="Mycological observations: 17 - 20, nomenclatural notes on some omphaloid genera in Canada: Chrysomphalina, Rickenella, Gerronema, Omphalina. Acta Mycologica Sinica Suppl: 297 - 304." year="1986">Redhead 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Norvell, L" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="379 - 407" refId="B44" refString="Norvell, L, Redhead, S, Ammirati, J, 1994. Omphalina sensu lato in North America 1-2. 1: Omphalina wynniae and the genus Chrysomphalina. 2: Omphalina sensu Bigelow. Mycotaxon 50: 379 - 407" title="Omphalina sensu lato in North America 1 - 2. 1: Omphalina wynniae and the genus Chrysomphalina. 2: Omphalina sensu Bigelow." volume="50" year="1994">Norvell et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Four species with a yellow pileus have been recorded: 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. keralense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="keralense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. keralense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. kuruvense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="kuruvense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. kuruvense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. strombodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="strombodes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. strombodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Flora Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 84" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" refId="B56" refString="Singer, R, 1970. Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes). Flora Neotropica 3: 1 - 84, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" title="Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" volume="3" year="1970">Singer 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" author="Takashi, O" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Society of Grassland Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="31 - 36" refId="B61" refString="Takashi, O, 2009. Decomposition of grass leaves by ligninolytic litter-decomposing fungi. Japanese Society of Grassland Science 56: 31 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" title="Decomposition of grass leaves by ligninolytic litter-decomposing fungi." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-697X.2009.00170.x" volume="56" year="2009">Takashi 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 11" refId="B2" refString="Antonin, V, Beran, M, Borovicka, J, Dvorak, D, Holec, J, 2011. Clitocybula familia (Fungi, Agaricales) - taxonomy, distribution, ecology and first records in the Czech Republic and Slovakia. Czech Mycology 63 (1): 1 - 11, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" title="Clitocybula familia (Fungi, Agaricales) - taxonomy, distribution, ecology and first records in the Czech Republic and Slovakia." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.63101" volume="63" year="2011">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" author="Latha, KPD" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="081 - 091" refId="B30" refString="Latha, KPD, Nanu, S, Sharafudheen, SA, Manimohan, P, 2018. Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India. Phytotaxa 364 (1): 081 - 091, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" title="Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" volume="364" year="2018">Latha et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" author="Takahashi, H" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="15 - 23" refId="B60" refString="Takahashi, H, 2000. Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan. Mycoscience 41 (1): 15 - 23, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" title="Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" volume="41" year="2000">Takahashi 2000</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema nemorale" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from Japan and later reported from the Republic of Korea, has the most morphological similarities to 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. baishanzuense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="baishanzuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. baishanzuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, the former differs in having a smaller pileus (&lt;20 mm in diameter) but a longer stipe (up to 40 mm), terminal elements less than 37 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, and much smaller caulocystidia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" author="Takahashi, H" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="15 - 23" refId="B60" refString="Takahashi, H, 2000. Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan. Mycoscience 41 (1): 15 - 23, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" title="Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" volume="41" year="2000">Takahashi 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="197 - 212" refId="B1" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2008. Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea. Czech Mycology 60 (2): 197 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" title="Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" volume="60" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast to 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. baishanzuense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="baishanzuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. baishanzuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two new species recently reported from the Indian state of Kerala, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. keralense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="keralense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. keralense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. kuruvense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="kuruvense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. kuruvense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are easily mistaken for the new species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" author="Latha, KPD" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="081 - 091" refId="B30" refString="Latha, KPD, Nanu, S, Sharafudheen, SA, Manimohan, P, 2018. Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India. Phytotaxa 364 (1): 081 - 091, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" title="Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" volume="364" year="2018">Latha et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). However, the pileus of 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. keralense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="keralense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. keralense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks dark brown fibrillose or pubescent, has smaller and slightly thick-walled cheilocystidia, and the hyphae of its stipitipellis and caulocystidia are both thin- to thick-walled (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" author="Latha, KPD" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="081 - 091" refId="B30" refString="Latha, KPD, Nanu, S, Sharafudheen, SA, Manimohan, P, 2018. Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India. Phytotaxa 364 (1): 081 - 091, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" title="Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" volume="364" year="2018">Latha et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema kuruvense" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="kuruvense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema kuruvense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is always distinctly yellow, has small basidiomata (pileus &lt;11 mm in diameter) and true pileocystidia, and lacks cheilocystidia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" author="Latha, KPD" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="081 - 091" refId="B30" refString="Latha, KPD, Nanu, S, Sharafudheen, SA, Manimohan, P, 2018. Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India. Phytotaxa 364 (1): 081 - 091, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" title="Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" volume="364" year="2018">Latha et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Finally, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. strombodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="strombodes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. strombodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distributed in North America and Asia, differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. baishanzuense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="baishanzuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. baishanzuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having larger basidiomata, a white to grayish white pileus (up to 80 mm wide), smooth pileipellis hyphae, and the absence of hymenial cystidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Flora Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 84" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" refId="B56" refString="Singer, R, 1970. Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes). Flora Neotropica 3: 1 - 84, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" title="Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" volume="3" year="1970">Singer 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="197 - 212" refId="B1" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2008. Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea. Czech Mycology 60 (2): 197 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" title="Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" volume="60" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" author="Kim, CS" journalOrPublisher="Mycobiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="22 - 26" refId="B24" refString="Kim, CS, Jo, JW, Kwag, YN, Han, JG, Shrestha, B, Sung, GH, Han, SK, 2014. Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea. Mycobiology 42 (1): 22 - 26, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" title="Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" volume="42" year="2014">Kim et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. citrinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="citrinum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. citrinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Corner) Pegler (
<bibRefCitation author="Pegler, DN" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin Additional Series IX, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B48" refString="Pegler, DN, 1983. Agaric flora of the Lesser Antilles. Kew Bulletin Additional Series IX, London" title="Agaric flora of the Lesser Antilles." year="1983">Pegler 1983</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. tenue" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="tenue">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. tenue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dennis (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" author="Dennis, RWG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="67 - 156" refId="B14" refString="Dennis, RWG, 1961. Fungi Venezuelani: IV Agaricales. Kew Bulletin 15 (1): 67 - 156, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" title="Fungi Venezuelani: IV Agaricales." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" volume="15" year="1961">Dennis 1961</bibRefCitation>
), are allied with 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. baishanzuense" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="baishanzuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. baishanzuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but their lamellae edges without cheilocystidia. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. citrinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="citrinum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. citrinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a relatively larger pileus (20-30 mm in diam.) and smaller basidiospores (6-7.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. tenue" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="tenue">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. tenue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having a citrine yellow pileus and an insititious stipe (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" author="Dennis, RWG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="67 - 156" refId="B14" refString="Dennis, RWG, 1961. Fungi Venezuelani: IV Agaricales. Kew Bulletin 15 (1): 67 - 156, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" title="Fungi Venezuelani: IV Agaricales." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" volume="15" year="1961">Dennis 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pegler, DN" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin Additional Series IX, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B48" refString="Pegler, DN, 1983. Agaric flora of the Lesser Antilles. Kew Bulletin Additional Series IX, London" title="Agaric flora of the Lesser Antilles." year="1983">Pegler 1983</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. hungo" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="hungo">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. hungo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Henn.) Degreef &amp; Eyi, reported by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.1502" author="Degreef, J" journalOrPublisher="Mycologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="171 - 176" refId="B13" refString="Degreef, J, Ndong, HE, 2007. Gerronema hungo, a comb. nov. for a poorly known central African edible mushroom. Cryptogamie. Mycologie 28 (3): 171 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.1502" title="Gerronema hungo, a comb. nov. for a poorly known central African edible mushroom. Cryptogamie." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/yea.1502" volume="28" year="2007">Degreef and Ndong (2007)</bibRefCitation>
as a new combination, differs in yellowish orange to brownish orange pileus, ellipsoid basidiospores, and absent cheilocystidia.
</paragraph>
